        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-08-27T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-08-27T15:00:00-05:00" n="606" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d606">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">821.796/8–2746: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wiley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-08-27T15:00:00-05:00">August 27, 1946—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>613. Re <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 606, August 24. It now appears
                    that four ex-<gloss target="#t_Scadta1">Scadta</gloss> pilots have already been
                    relicensed as copilots. I made very strong representations to Foreign Minister
                    yesterday. He expressed entire agreement with my point of view and stated that
                    President had already spoken to him and that the President had stated he was
                    going to confer at once with Minister of War. Shall report further
                    developments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wiley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
